{
  "message": "Add extension crate stubs: fts3, fts5, rtree, json, session, icu, misc\n\nSeven crates providing SQLite's loadable extension equivalents as\ncompile-time modules. Each depends on fsqlite-types and fsqlite-error.\n\nfsqlite-ext-fts3:\n- FTS3 and FTS4 full-text search with porter stemmer, tokenizers,\n  and the matchinfo/snippet/offsets auxiliary functions\n\nfsqlite-ext-fts5:\n- FTS5 next-generation full-text search with BM25 ranking, custom\n  tokenizers, and the highlight/snippet auxiliary functions\n\nfsqlite-ext-rtree:\n- R-tree spatial index for bounding-box queries, plus the geopoly\n  extension for polygon containment and overlap queries\n\nfsqlite-ext-json:\n- JSON1 functions (json, json_extract, json_set, json_remove,\n  json_array, json_object, json_each, json_tree, etc.)\n- Additional dep: serde_json for JSON parsing/serialization\n\nfsqlite-ext-session:\n- Session extension for recording database changes as changesets\n  and patchsets, enabling diff/merge/rebase of database state\n\nfsqlite-ext-icu:\n- ICU collation sequences for locale-aware string comparison\n  and case folding\n\nfsqlite-ext-misc:\n- Miscellaneous virtual tables and functions: generate_series,\n  carray, dbstat (page-level statistics), and dbpage (raw page access)\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
